'''Bruno Bernard Joseph Odon Louis'''(born 9 February 1966 in [[Rouvreux]]) is a writer on international trade.
== Biography == Bernard has appeared on the Russian television news channel [[RT (TV network)|RT]] to discuss international trade.<ref>{{Citation|title = Bruno Bernard Interview with RT TV international|url = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=L2jk0B8DO14|date = 2014-08-25|accessdate = 2016-02-08|last = RTQuestionMore}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title = Commercial expert |url = http://ec.europa.eu/transparencyregister/public/consultation/displaylobbyist.do?id=702292810142-25&isListLobbyistView=true}}</ref> He is a professor and senior lecturer in several universities (Paris Dauphine, University of Lorraine, UMons, Caucasus University,<ref>{{Citation|title = Caucasus University Biography |url = https://cu.edu.ge/files/Docs/CU/Doctor%20Honoris/Bruno_BErnard_Bio.pdf}}</ref> ECS Brussels, Groningen University,<ref>{{Citation|title = University of Groningen |url = https://www.rug.nl/let/agenda-2018/la-francophonie}}</ref> Raboud University ...), and has published works on export and business ethics in twelve languages.
