{{Infobox member of the Knesset |image = |birth_date = 26 April 1946 |birth_place = [[Tel Aviv]], [[Mandatory Palestine]] |death_date = {{Death date and age|1988|10|27|1946|4|26|df=y}} |death_place = |Knesset(s) = [[Israeli legislative election, 1981|10]], [[Israeli legislative election, 1984|11]] |party1 = [[Likud]] |partyyears1 = 1981–1988 }}
'''Michael "Mikha" Reisser''' ({{Lang-he|מיכאל רייסר}}, 26 April 1946 &ndash; 27 October 1988) was an [[Israel]]i politician who served as a member of the [[Knesset]] for [[Likud]] between 1981 and his death in 1988.
==Biography== Born in [[Tel Aviv]] towards the end of the [[Mandatory Palestine|Mandate era]], Reisser was educated at the Shalva [[Gymnasium (school)|gymnasium]], before studying sociology and labour studies at [[Tel Aviv University]]. He became chairman of the university's student union in 1970, and from 1971 until 1977 chaired the secretariat of the [[Herut]] young guard.
In 1978 he started working as a consultant to the [[Immigrant Absorption Minister of Israel|Minister of Immigrant Absorption]] and [[Housing and Construction Minister of Israel|Minister of Housing]]. He went on to become deputy director of the Housing Ministry and director of the Israel Builders Association from 1979 until 1981. He also became chairman of the board at HaYekev in 1981, and was a member of the board at the Ata textiles company from 1981 until 1984.
From 1979 until 1980 he chaired Herut's Organisation Department. The following year he was [[Israeli legislative election, 1981|elected]] to the Knesset on the Likud list (then an alliance of Herut and other right-wing parties). He was re-elected in [[Israeli legislative election, 1984|1984]], and became chairman of the House Committee. However, on 26 October 1988, he was fatally injured in a car crash whilst on a journey to [[Jerusalem]] for a photoshoot for the [[Israeli legislative election, 1988|upcoming elections]] when his car crashed into another car being driven by future politician [[Dalia Itzik]],<ref>[http://www.nrg.co.il/online/1/ART/863/595.html Itzik power] NRG, 4 February 2005</ref> and died of his injuries the following day. His Knesset seat was taken by [[David Mor]].<ref>[https://www.knesset.gov.il/mk/eng/mkindexbyknesset_eng.asp?knesset=11 Knesset Members in the Eleventh Knesset] Knesset website</ref>
Reisser was married with a son and twin daughters. All three of his children became religious after his death.
[[Beitar Avraham Be'er Sheva F.C.|Beitar Avraham Be'er Sheva's]] stadium, a junior high school and winery club in [[Rishon LeZion]], streets in [[Lod]] and [[Ramla]], and a playground in [[Nahariya]] are named after him.
